<br>
Personally, if I had a choice between the two, I think I'd go for Fiery Defender based on the fact that AC is less important to me as I progress because I'm NEVER the main tank in a group or on a raid, and I like the damage, look, and prestige of weilding the epic (not that I am yet).<br>
<br>
If you're looking for a Paladin weapon that you don't have to quest for, I'd recommend arbitor's combine greatsword for a 2hs.  IMO they are undervalued on the server, have great damage/delay ratio for a paladin usable sword, and a great wis bonus to boot.  Almost the perfect mid level Paladin 2hs as far as i'm concerned.<br>
<br>
On a side note, don't discount 1hs weapons.  The ability of a Paladin to bash for interrupts is very important in the mid levels and until you start carrying uberswords, you have to have 1hs to do that.  The two end all be all Paladin usable 1hs that come to mind to me are the Sword of Morning and Darkmetal Falchion.  Both of these are not easy to get, you have to have a lot of plat laying around for the sword of morning and a LOT of patience waiting on someone who is willing to part with theirs, or get REALLY lucky on a Hate raid to win the roll on a rare drop that is wanted by Paladins and SKs alike.  Even halycon broadsword, another really nice 1hs is almost impossible to obtain since it is the really really rare drop off of the only mob worth hunting in SF mountains, and that mob is pretty much unthinkable to engage until you are at a level that you probably have a pretty decent weapon already.  <br>
<br>
This leaves the problem that there is quite a shortage of good 1hs weapons for a paladin, especially in the paladin-only category.  I know there have been some improvements since velious, but I don't know much about them.  If you can stand the weight (i.e. sta drain) of a wurmslayer, go for it.  If you are skilled enough to use the sword of skyfire without killing yourself once it starts procing and smart enough not to use it in a mesing group or a layered dungeon, i prefer it as primary weapon as long as i have a standbye when the ae proc on skyfire is inappropriate for the place/group i'm hunting.<br>
<br>
One other side note.  Laugh if you want, but imo, for a midlevel paladin, you simply can't beat a Mith 2H for damage/delay for the price.  That is still a really nice sword and i don't care if the price continues to drop until they're under 1K, i'd STILL carry that thing with no shame if i hadn't managed to finally get into some weapons that will out damage it.  Another bonus to weilding the mith 2h is it lets you put off buying a haste item much longer, since the haste on the mith doesn't stack with other haste items.<br>
<br>
In general, all i can say is DON'T try using your soulfire if you can afford a mith instead.  put it in the bank and take it to social functions.  DON'T use your ghoulbane unless you're in an undead zone.  And DON'T get caught up in the &quot;expensive is better&quot; myth of EC.  Look at the damage/delay (faster is better even if you have to sacrifice damage when you're still trying to max your 1hs and 2hs skills imo), look at where you hunt (if it's a weapon with a proc), keep your slashing skills (at a minimum) up, and weild a sword that you are proud of, ignoring the comments of the uber-twinked ebay equipped morons that slam people for not buying their way into nice equipment.  =)<br>
<br>
